{{New unreviewed article|source=ArticleWizard|date=April 2011}}

[[Image:Kamochi_Jinja.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Torii]] and path leading to Kamochi Jinja]]

{{nihongo|'''Kamochi Jinja'''|金持神社}} is an ancient [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Hino, Tottori|Hino]], [[Tottori Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. Its name is regarded as auspicious.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kanemochi-jinja.net/modules/tinyd0/ |title=Kamochi Jinja - History |publisher=Kamochi Jinja |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://yokoso.pref.tottori.jp/dd.aspx?menuid=1893 |title=Kamochi Jinja |publisher=[[Tottori Prefecture]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.town.hino.tottori.jp/dd.aspx?menuid=1281 |title=Kamochi Jinja |publisher=[[Hino, Tottori|Hino Town]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>

